      "id": "PopularPost108648",
      "post_content": "**Aaron's Random Card Comment of the Day #10, 10/8/10**   \n   \nLord of the Pit is one of those transcendent **Magic** cards that has spawned an entire category of followers; his legion of gigantic black rares that eat your own creatures includes [Ebon Praetor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ebon Praetor), [Doomgape](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doomgape), [Devouring Strossus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Devouring Strossus), [Minion of Leshrac](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Minion of Leshrac), and the most recent update, [Xathrid Demon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Xathrid Demon).\n  \n   \nCards like Lord of the Pit\u2014and other genre-spawning icons like [Juz\u00e1m Djinn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Juz\u00e1m Djinn), [Ball Lightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning), and [Masticore](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Masticore)\u2014hit some kind of note with players (and designers) that just feels right for **Magic**, they have some unique quality that people latch on to and generally have good memories of, and thusly are worth trying to imitate time and again, even if they aren\u2019t the most powerful cards in the game. Lord of the Pit (and [Demonic Hordes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Hordes)) defined Demons as... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Aaron_Forsythe",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost108648\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\"><b>Aaron's Random Card Comment of the Day #10, 10/8/10</b> <br/> <br/>Lord of the Pit is one of those transcendent <b>Magic </b>cards that has spawned an entire category of followers; his legion of gigantic black rares that eat your own creatures includes <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ebon Praetor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ebon Praetor\">Ebon Praetor</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Doomgape\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doomgape\">Doomgape</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Devouring Strossus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Devouring Strossus\">Devouring Strossus</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Minion of Leshrac\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Minion of Leshrac\">Minion of Leshrac</a>, and the most recent update, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Xathrid Demon\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Xathrid Demon\">Xathrid Demon</a>.\r<br/> <br/>Cards like Lord of the Pit\u2014and other genre-spawning icons like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Juz\u00e1m Djinn\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Juz\u00e1m Djinn\">Juz\u00e1m Djinn</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ball Lightning\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning\">Ball Lightning</a>, and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Masticore\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Masticore\">Masticore</a>\u2014hit some kind of note with players (and designers) that just feels right for <b>Magic</b>, they have some unique quality that people latch on to and generally have good memories of, and thusly are worth trying to imitate time and again, even if they aren\u2019t the most powerful cards in the game. Lord of the Pit (and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Demonic Hordes\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Hordes\">Demonic Hordes</a>) defined Demons as... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 108648)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '108648'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy5180\">Aaron_Forsythe</span>\r\n                                (10/8/2010 1:40:58 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br 