      "id": "PopularPost157511",
      "post_content": "It's still a beast in casual play. I run a black/white deck with three LoP and a few things that can prevent the upkeep damage if necessary, like [Circle of Protection: Black](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Protection: Black). Just for grins I've also got [Samite Ministration](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Samite Ministration) with which I can gain 7 life instead of taking 7 damage for one turn. And of course some oldschool black mana acceleration.  \nNow, on the rulings - I've always played it with the Circle of Protection and just paid 1 instead of sacking a creature. I guess I can only do this if I do not have any creatures?",
      "posted_by": "jfre81",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost157511\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">It's still a beast in casual play. I run a black/white deck with three LoP and a few things that can prevent the upkeep damage if necessary, like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Circle of Protection: Black\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Protection: Black\">Circle of Protection: Black</a>. Just for grins I've also got <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Samite Ministration\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Samite Ministration\">Samite Ministration</a> with which I can gain 7 life instead of taking 7 damage for one turn. And of course some oldschool black mana acceleration.<br/>Now, on the rulings - I've always played it with the Circle of Protection and just paid 1 instead of sacking a creature. I guess I can only do this if I do not have any creatures?</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '157511'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy59706\">jfre81</span>\r\n                                (5/9/2011 9:44:08 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                             