    {
      "id": "PopularPost166304",
      "post_content": "@ Aaron:  \nAfter I have commented other replies from \"Random Card Comment\", I want to repeat myself here once.  \nThe Lord of the Pit is an icon, a symbol... that's true. But his real status was always ignored due to the fact that black is the color of creature sacrifice, but was **never ever** the color of creature hordes (production).  \n  \nTherefore the god of evil was combined with white protection or green token mechanic & mana acceleration. Only rarely, it was combined with Thrulls, the underwhelming [Breeding Pit](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Breeding Pit) or [Sengir Autocrat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Autocrat). The ever-present [Swords to Plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares) was also a big problem.   \n  \nBut what I really liked in your post:  \n*Lord of the Pit (and Demonic Hordes) defined Demons as having a **downside** attached to an undercosted threatening body, and that blueprint has served us well over the years for making fun, flavorful cards; even though **most players** would rather not have drawbacks on their cards at a*... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Cheza",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost166304\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">@ Aaron:<br/>After I have commented other replies from \"Random Card Comment\", I want to repeat myself here once.<br/>The Lord of the Pit is an icon, a symbol... that's true. But his real status was always ignored due to the fact that black is the color of creature sacrifice, but was <b>never ever</b> the color of creature hordes (production).<br/><br/>Therefore the god of evil was combined with white protection or green token mechanic &amp; mana acceleration. Only rarely, it was combined with Thrulls, the underwhelming <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Breeding Pit\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Breeding Pit\">Breeding Pit</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sengir Autocrat\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Autocrat\">Sengir Autocrat</a>. The ever-present <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Swords to Plowshares\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares\">Swords to Plowshares</a> was also a big problem. <br/><br/>But what I really liked in your post:<br/><i>Lord of the Pit (and Demonic Hordes) defined Demons as having a <b>downside</b> attached to an undercosted threatening body, and that blueprint has served us well over the years for making fun, flavorful cards; even though <b>most players</b> would rather not have drawbacks on their cards at a</i>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 166304)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '166304'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1148\">Cheza</span>\r\n                                (6/4/2011 6:54:01 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
